        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tools): surface empty availability group diagnostics at descriptor registration",
        "body": "> **AI-assisted PR.** Implemented and verified with Claude (Claude Code). I have reviewed and understand the change and own the final diff.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Empty `allOf`/`anyOf` availability groups silently hid tools from the plan with no observable signal. Plugin authors had no way to know their descriptor was malformed.\n- Root cause: `capturePluginToolDescriptor` did not preserve tool-authored `availability` expressions, and no validation ran at registration time.\n- Fix: preserve `availability` on captured descriptors and surface `unsupported-signal` diagnostics via `console.warn` once at descriptor-registration time (not in the planner hot path).\n\nFixes #92361\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\n**Behavior addressed**:\nMalformed tool descriptors with empty availability groups now produce a visible `console.warn` at descriptor-registration time instead of silently hiding the tool with no signal.\n\n**Real environment tested**:\nLinux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, Node.js v24.13.1, OpenClaw PR branch @ d8907360, tsx for runtime probing.\n\n**Before-fix evidence**:\n```text\n# Empty anyOf → tool silently hidden, no warning, no log\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { capturePluginToolDescriptor } from './src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.js';\ncapturePluginToolDescriptor({\n  pluginId: 'proof-plugin',\n  tool: { name: 'proof_tool', description: 'test', parameters: { type: 'object' }, availability: { anyOf: [] } } as any,\n  optional: false,\n});\nconsole.log('No warning was emitted — tool silently captured with broken availability');\n\"\n# Output: No warning was emitted — tool silently captured with broken availability\n```\n\nThe tool descriptor is captured and later hidden by `buildToolPlan` with zero observable signal. Plugin authors have no way to diagnose why their tool never appears in the plan.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { capturePluginToolDescriptor } from './src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.js';\n\n// Test 1: empty anyOf\ncapturePluginToolDescriptor({\n  pluginId: 'proof-plugin',\n  tool: { name: 'proof_tool', description: 'test', parameters: { type: 'object' }, availability: { anyOf: [] } } as any,\n  optional: false,\n});\n\n// Test 2: empty allOf\ncapturePluginToolDescriptor({\n  pluginId: 'proof-plugin',\n  tool: { name: 'allof_tool', description: 'test', parameters: { type: 'object' }, availability: { allOf: [] } } as any,\n  optional: false,\n});\n\n// Test 3: valid expression (no warning expected)\ncapturePluginToolDescriptor({\n  pluginId: 'proof-plugin',\n  tool: { name: 'valid_tool', description: 'test', parameters: { type: 'object' }, availability: { kind: 'always' } } as any,\n  optional: false,\n});\n\"\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```text\n[plugins] tool descriptor authoring error (proof-plugin/proof_tool): Empty availability anyOf group\n[plugins] tool descriptor authoring error (proof-plugin/allof_tool): Empty availability allOf group\n```\n\n- Empty `anyOf` → `console.warn` emitted with pluginId + tool name + diagnostic message ✅\n- Empty `allOf` → `console.warn` emitted with pluginId + tool name + diagnostic message ✅\n- Valid `kind: \"always\"` → no warning (correctly silent) ✅\n- No availability → no warning (backward compatible) ✅\n\n**Observed result after the fix**:\nDescriptor authors immediately see which tool has a malformed availability expression at registration time (once per captured descriptor — descriptors are cached). The evaluator and planner stay pure.\n\n**What was not tested**:\nLive gateway startup with a real external plugin that has malformed availability metadata. The descriptor capture path operates on in-memory descriptors and has no platform-specific logic.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tool-descriptor-cache.test.ts\n# Test Files  1 passed (1)\n# Tests       10 passed (10)\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts\n# Test Files  1 passed (1)\n# Tests       67 passed (67)\n\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tools/planner.test.ts\n# Test Files  1 passed (1)\n# Tests       6 passed (6)\n\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental false\n# passed\n```\n\nNew test cases:\n1. warns when tool has empty availability `anyOf` group\n2. warns when tool has empty availability `allOf` group\n3. does not warn for valid availability expression\n4. does not warn when tool has no availability\n5. does not warn for non-expression availability metadata\n6. preserves availability on the captured descriptor\n\n## Risk / scope\n\n- User-visible behavior change: No — descriptors are a developer contract, not user-facing runtime behavior\n- Config/environment/migration: No\n- Security/auth/network: No\n- Highest risk: `console.warn` fires once per captured descriptor at registration time. Descriptors are cached after first capture, so the warning fires exactly once per unique tool per cache lifetime.\n- Mitigation: `unsupported-signal` only fires for malformed descriptors (empty allOf/anyOf, unknown expression shapes). Runtime conditions like auth-missing are explicitly excluded.\n\n## What did NOT change (scope boundary)\n\n- `evaluateToolAvailability` / `evaluateExpression` — still pure, no side effects\n- `buildToolPlan` — still a deterministic planner, no callbacks\n- `AnyAgentTool` type — no new contract field; reading through narrowed record (same pattern as existing `label` read)\n- Plugin SDK exports — no public API surface change\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
